    • CoronaResults

      public CoronaResults(List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbCondition> listConditions, List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbObservation> listObservations, List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbPatient> listPatients, List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter> listEncounters, List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbProcedure> listIcuProcedures, List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbLocation> listLocations)
      Initialization of the CoronaResults object with the required FhirRessource lists.
      Parameters:
      listConditions - List of FHIR condition resources for U07.1 and U07.2 diagnoses
      listObservations - List of FHIR Observation Resources based on the Corona Lab Codes
      listPatients - List of FHIR patient resources based on the Condition and Observation inputs
      listEncounters - List of FHIR encounter resources based on the Condition and Observation inputs
      listIcuProcedures - List of FHIR ICU procedures resources based on the Patient/Encounter inputs
      listLocations - List of all FHIR location resources based on the encounter inputs

  • Method Details

    • getDataItems

      public ArrayList<CoronaDataItem> getDataItems(Map<String,Boolean> mapExcludeDataItems, Boolean debug, VariantSettings variantSettings, InputCodeSettings inputCodeSettings)
      Creation of the JSON specification file for the Corona dashboard based on FHIR resources.
      Parameters:
      mapExcludeDataItems - Map with data items to be excluded from the output (e.g. "current.treatmentlevel").
      debug - Flag to provide debug information (e.g. casenrs) in the output.
      variantSettings - Configuration of extended covid variants for the definition of not yet known/captured variants.
      inputCodeSettings - The configuration of the parameterizable codes such as the observation codes or procedure codes.
      Returns:
      List with all the data items that are defined in the corona dashboard json specification
